article.headline: IUPUI 89, Chicago St. 75
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Junior Gary Patterson scored 27 points to lead IUPUI to a 89-75 win over Chicago State on Wednesday night in nonconference play. Senior Austin Montgomery had 25 points, including four 3-pointers, and George Hill added 19 points and five assists for IUPUI (23-6, 15-3 Summit League), which moved closer to the school record of 24 wins in a season with the victory. Chicago State (11-17) led 41-34 at the half, but IUPUI came back, shooting 20-of-29 from the field, or 69 percent, in the second half. That was compared with 12-of-29 from the field, or 41 percent, for Chicago State. David Holston had 27 points, including five 3-pointers, and added a game-high eight assists for Chicago State. John Cantrell scored 23 points and Chidozie Chukwumah added 10 points and nine rebounds for the Cougars. IUPUI swept the two-game series with Chicago State. The Jaguars beat the Cougars 78-70 on Nov. 24 in Indianapolis.
